.Proc APODIZE  
[1mAPODIZE[0m  - Modifies picture borders so that the Fourier transform 
           will be free from spikes through the zero frequency axis, allowing 
           filters to operate without ringing on the edge of an image.
.Proc FFT1
[1mFFT1[0m     - Procedure computing forward and inverse complex 1-D 
           Fourier transforms.
.Proc FFT1PIX
[1mFFT1PIX[0m  - Displays an amplitude and/or phase picture of input 
           Fourier transform. Permits modification of the Fourier transform.
.Proc FFT2
[1mFFT2[0m     - Procedure computing forward and inverse complex 2-D 
           Fourier transforms.
.Proc FFTCLAS
[1mFFTCLAS[0m  - Analyzes halfword FFT images producing 5 attribute values
           for each FFT examined. 
.Proc FFTFIT
[1mFFTFIT[0m   - Modifies complex Fourier Transforms (FT) by either 
           multiplying the FT by an input image or by making the amplitude
           of the FT proportional to an input image.

